  </span></div><div class="a-row"><a class="a-link-normal" href="/gp/review/R1O98SS7T8YXDK/ref=cm_cr_pr_rvw_ttl?ASIN=B000065DJY"><i class="a-icon a-icon-star a-star-1 review-rating"></i></a><span class="a-letter-space"></span><a class="a-link-normal review-title a-color-base a-text-normal a-text-bold" href="/gp/review/R1O98SS7T8YXDK/ref=cm_cr_pr_rvw_ttl?ASIN=B000065DJY">Stay away from the dryer... stay away...</a></div><div class="a-row"><span class="review-byline"><span class="a-color-secondary">By </span><a class="a-link-normal" href="/gp/pdp/profile/A3S9CWLFBXXNYW/ref=cm_cr_pr_pdp">Amazon Customer</a></span><span class="a-declarative" data-action="cr-popup" data-cr-popup="{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Help&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:&quot;340&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:&quot;340&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/gp/help/customer/display.html/ref=cm_cr_dp_bdg_help?ie=UTF8&amp;nodeId=14279681&amp;pop-up=1#tr&quot;}"></span><span class="a-letter-space"></span><span class="a-color-secondary review-date">on Thu Mar 09 13:59:20 UTC 2006</span></div><div class="a-row a-spacing-top-mini review-data"><div class="a-section">



  I loved it at first... I thought it was GOOD that it got so hot that my hair held its shape better.  Gradually I started noticing more and more breakage from the heat damage.  OK, don't use it on the highest setting, lesson learned.  After about a month of not quite daily use, the thing started shooting out SPARKS.  I'm not about to aim something that does that at my head.  So... it never died, but it did become possessed, so some element of the afterlife is definitely evident.  This thing is a hair-singeing, spark-shooting weapon, folks.  If you buy it, use it for something other than what it was designed for or you'll be bald and blind!!!
